main event: The report details multiple sightings of unidentified flying objects (UFOs) on May 17, 1956 and July 2, 1956 in Ada, Oklahoma, with witnesses observing around 20 disk-shaped objects of small size and estimated speeds of 1000-1500 M.P.H.
interesting points: Witnesses observed approximately 20 UFOs, each rounded in shape and the size of a pea, with a projection in the center and estimated to be between 50 to 100 feet in size.
One of the witnesses believed that the objects were under intelligent control and were positively some sort of machine.
The report includes witness information such as name, address, and age of the person who claimed to have seen the objects.
The sightings took place in broad daylight with clear skies, and the brightness and disappearance of the objects were compared to the position of the sun and the presence of clouds.

The handwritten material suggests that the objects were solid, had a silver-grey color, and displayed a shadow or protrusion in the center, with sharp outlines and estimated brightness duller than the sun.
